content.description: Start on the right side of the rock in the woods, and climb up and to the left before pulling over the top. Make sure you look for holds as you pull over the top.
content.protection: Crash pad would be nice as it sometimes gets a little muddy in the cave.
content.location: On the second rock in the woods, pull yourself up and over the top.

content.description: Pulling yourself up and over the overhang can be quite a challenge with a fun little heel hook and quite the arm pump afterwards.
content.protection: Crash Matt is always nice, but the landing is squishy with no real problems. Just don't roll down the little hill if you fall.
content.location: On the second rock in the woods, start sitting on the ground on the right side of the boulder next to the protruding corner. Haul yourself up and over the boulder for a nice pump.

content.description: Leads up the obvious rock by the road. Follow the crack up and along to the top of the boulder. Fun, slabby and a little intimidating, its a great problem!
content.protection: Landing can be a little rough with a slanting rock right below. If your gonna take a fall, push off and land on the gravel so you don't roll your ankle.
content.location: Obvious boulder hanging over the side of the road.

content.description: Start sitting on your butt as deep into the little cave as you can get, and shimmy your way out while underclinging the roof above your head. The route is quite crammed and during parts you may even find yourself using your head to keep you from peeling. Climb out and around the top of the boulder.
content.protection: Close to the ground the whole way, a crash pad might be nice as sometimes it can get a little muddy in the cave, but otherwise the problem should be worry free.
content.location: On the second rock a little up into the woods, the problem leads out of as deep as you can in the cave along the crease on the left side then out and over.

content.description: Two boulders off the side of Route 11 near Dewey Beach with some great little problems. The more obvious boulder is about 20 feet tall leaning over the side of the road. The rock is kinda sharp but fun none the less. The other boulder is up and to the right a few feet into the woods. This little cave you found has quite a few fun problems leading out and over the top.
